olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 leek
1 carrot
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Mushroom Powder
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet risotto-style rice
2.25 cup boiling water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
20 g butter
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Rocket leaves
drizzle balsamic vinegar

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Boil the kettle.
• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice leek. Finely chop carrot.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add leek and carrot and cook, stirring, until tender, 4-5 minutes.

• Add garlic, mushroom powder, tomato paste and risotto-style rice and cook, stirring until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the boiling water (21/4 cups for 2 people / 41/2 cups for 4 people) and chicken-style stock powder, then bring to the boil.
• Transfer risotto to a baking dish. Cover tightly with foil. Bake until liquid is absorbed and rice is ‘al dente’, 24-28 minutes.

TIP: ‘Al dente’ rice is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

• When the risotto is ready, stir through the butter and half the gratedParmesan cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
• Meanwhile, combine rocket leaves and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

TIP: Stir through a splash of water if the risotto looks dry!

• Divide beef, pork and leek bolognese risotto between bowls.
• Sprinkle over remaining Parmesan cheese.
• Serve with balsamic rocket salad. Enjoy!